# Whitelist repo: everything is ignored, then the source we WANT backed up is re-added.
# Rationale: this folder holds ~130 one-off pipeline scripts, JSON dumps and private strategy docs.
# An allow-list is the only way a future `git add -A` cannot leak something by accident.
*

# --- the app itself ---
!poker-trainer.html
!wrap.js
!package.json
!package-lock.json

# --- tests ---
!test-*.js

# --- context for Claude ---
!CLAUDE.md
!SOURCE-BRANCH.md
!.gitignore

# NEVER un-ignore these, they are private and live in the vault instead:
#   Q1-* Q2-* Q3-*            monetization / anti-copy / extraction strategy
#   WINDOW-*                  per-window kickoff docs
#   *-contract.md             hand-extraction methodology
#   deploy/                   nested clone of the same repo (branch main)
